# 2026-06-15 15:54:25.971446
+There's a bug in llm.py strip_think(). Qwen3-32B emits literal <think>...</think> tags (you can see them in your own output above), NOT 《思考》/《回答》. Fix strip_think() to remove everything between <think> and </think>:
+
+    def strip_think(text):
+        return re.sub(r"<think>.*?</think>", "", text, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()
+
+Also parse_json should handle the case where </think> appears without an opening tag, and should extract the JSON object even if there's surrounding prose — find the first { and last } and parse that substring. Then RUN the test with: /run python llm.py  — and show me the actual output. The vLLM server IS running on port 8000, so the test should work now. Do not move on until it prints clean parsed JSON.Also: in chat(), you pass response_format both as a direct argument AND inside extra_body — remove it from extra_body, keep only the direct argument. And tools=None should not be passed when there are no tools (some vLLM versions reject tools=None) — only include tools in the call if it's not None.
